items.title: Exploring More Of The Backroads Of Washington
items.description:
exploretravel1 posted a photo:

Backroads Of Washington Are Amazing The backroads of Washington are amazing. Take any one of them and discover a mountain, a stream, or a lake. Mount Rainier is the highest mountain in the Cascade Range. It is just one of many stars in the Pacific Northwest. It is however, the shinning star of Washington State. Here […]

items.title: A Telephoto Close-Up Of Nisqually Glacier
items.description:
Where The Trails Take You Photography posted a photo:

It's Fun Fact Friday, so here's something for you courtesy of Mount Rainier National Park: Nisqually Glacier is the most-studied and easily-accessible glacier on The Mountain. And, Mount Rainier, itself, is the most heavily-glaciated peak in the contiguous U.S. Just look at those amazing crevasses on that river of ice, which looks kinda dirty, actually, because of all the rocks, boulders, and rock flour in and on top of the glacier.
